7 AS INTRODUCED
8 A Concurrent Resolution urging Oklahoma's
Congressional Delegation to Support the Credit for
9 Caring Act for family caregivers.
10
11
12 WHEREAS, family caregivers play a vital role in supporting loved
13 ones with long-term health needs, often bearing significant
14 financial and emotional burdens as they provide essential care; and
15 WHEREAS, the Credit for Caring Act seeks to provide a federal
16 tax credit of up to $5,000 annually to working family caregivers,
17 helping to offset the high costs of caregiving and alleviating
18 financial strain; and
19 WHEREAS, Oklahoma is home to an estimated 490,000 family
20 caregivers who collectively contribute over $6.6 billion in unpaid
21 care, providing critical support that allows many older Oklahomans
22 to remain in his or her home rather than move to costly
23 institutional care facilities; and
24
