1 WHEREAS, studies indicate that a significant number of family
2 caregivers nationwide report spending an average of more than $7,000
3 per year out-of-pocket on expenses for his or her loved ones,
4 including transportation, medical equipment, home modifications, in-
5 home care services, and respite care; and
6 WHEREAS, a large percentage of Oklahoma family caregivers face
7 similar financial challenges, as they are often required to cover
8 out-of-pocket costs for caregiving services while balancing work and
9 caregiving responsibilities; and
10 WHEREAS, without the contributions of family caregivers, many
11 older citizens would likely face higher costs associated with
12 institutionalized care, ultimately shifting the financial burden to
13 taxpayers and the state; and
14 WHEREAS, the Oklahoma Legislature has already demonstrated
15 leadership by passing the nation's first comprehensive state-based
16 caregiver tax credit, recognizing the need for policy solutions that
17 support family caregivers; and
18 WHEREAS, President Donald Trump has expressed his support for
19 family caregivers, and Oklahoma Representative Tom Cole has co-
20 sponsored the Credit for Caring Act, we urge our Congressional
21 Delegation to follow their lead by supporting the Credit for Caring
22 Act at the federal level.
